NUMBER 853
NAME Xerkataal
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_STARTYou stand upon a sheet of thick ice covered with snow. A bitter biting wind pierces through to your skin, cutting into you like sharp steel, and chilling you to the core. Far off to the north, through the haze and the driven snow, you can make out some kind of glittering mountain range. A large shimmering gate is here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 0 763  ADJ1=287  VAL2=2092
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 857
;
NUMBER 854
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stumble across the plane of ice, uncertain of where you are. The bitter wind carries flurries of snow making it very difficult to see any distance. The ground here is slick, and you have trouble keeping your footing. A fair distance to the north, mountains of ice glitter darkly.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 861
EXIT E 855
;
NUMBER 855
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The ground here dips into a hollow depression filled with snow. At its deepest it comes up to the level of your knees. The wind howls loudly... or was that some denizen of the frozen wastes? Off to the north through the bitter frozen air, you can discern some kind of an icy mountain range glittering in the faint light.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 862
EXIT E 856
EXIT W 854
;
NUMBER 856
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Blowing and falling snow covers your clothes, altering your appearence and making you begin to resemble one of the icy inhabitants of this realm. The unfriendly cold of this place reaches inwards, chilling you to the core, forcing you to keep moving to survive.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 863
EXIT E 857
EXIT W 855
IFENTRY
	APPEAR %s is covered with tiny flakes of snow.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 857
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A large patch of exposed ice shimmers faintly, a solid pond of whiteness surrounded by a great sea of dull grey snow. There are numerous scratch marks in the surface of the ice, and in several places, large chunks seem to have been eaten away. To the north, the icy mountain range looms closer.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 864
EXIT S 853
EXIT E 858
EXIT W 856
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER The type of tooth-mark in the ice here reminds you somewhat of the mouth structure of a Darakoth.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 858
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stumble onwards across the great glacier. The whistling of the bitter wind stings your ears as surely as the chill it carries bites your flesh. To the north, a mountain range of ice glitters like a diamond. Between you and it, however, many strange shapes move about on the snowy plain.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 865
EXIT E 859
EXIT W 857
;
NUMBER 859
NAME Monolith
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rising up from the ice here is some kind of a large stone monolith. You wonder about how it got here, but only briefly, as its motionless form provides you with a shelter from the constant driving wind which howls angrily about you. To the northwest lies the gleaming range of icy mountains, and you almost swear you can see strange figures dancing on its slopes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 0 44
ITEM 8 1567
EXTEND 0 monolith
EXIT N 866
EXIT W 858
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER There seems to be some kind of an inscription scrawled on the stone.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ 0
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR SKILL32 < 6
		ECHO PLAYER The runes seem to be in a language you don't recognize.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
		ECHO PLAYER The language of the runes is not one in common use in Andor... however you recognize it from your studies, and can piece together the meaning: "We hereby offer praise, blood and souls to our lord and master, Rakthaarn, lord of the frigid realms, and leave this monument as a testament to his glorious might."
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 860
NAME Wall of ice
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Wandering across this frigid plain, you suddenly come face to face with a wall of ice. It rises up further than you can see, completely blocking your way to the west. In the center of its crystalline face, there has been carved a single word, in large letters:
   "DOOM"
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT E 861
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 6
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You are reminded of a story you came across once, in an ancient text, long ago, about a place so hated by the gods that they covered it with a sheet of ice and left the mark of doom upon it so that men would know not to venture there.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
