NUMBER 862
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Whistling winds spin in tiny eddies, picking up drifts of snow and spinning them in rapid spirals about your head. The numbing cold is starting to get to you, making your head spin with strange visions of a nether reality. Small lights dance about in front of your eyes, and it is only by shaking your head and moving about that you can send them away.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 869
EXIT S 855
EXIT E 863
EXIT W 861
;
NUMBER 863
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
As the icy wind whips past, you hear a loud crack from close by. The ice perhaps? To the north a fair distance away, a giant mountain of ice rises. Above it in the grey sky overhead, you can just make out a shimmering aurora borealis. The combination of crystalline mountain and glowing light is one of the most beautiful things you have ever witnessed.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 870
EXIT S 856
EXIT E 864
EXIT W 863
;
NUMBER 864
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Walking across the plain, you notice that the ice here is oddly striated into bands of very faint subdued color. Subtle pastel reds and blues intermix with the occasional faded yellow and powder green. You have no idea how these colors got frozen into the ice, but what they imply about this place is somewhat frightening.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 871
EXIT S 857
EXIT E  865
EXIT W 863
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You seem to remember from somewhere that bands like this imply that the ice froze at different times; possibly seperated by thousands of years.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 865
NAME Xerkataal plain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The great frozen glacier continues, spreading out in all directions like fungus spreading over the forest floor. You think you see a dark figure emerge from the rushing winds, but then it reveals itself to be merely shifting shadows and eyestrain. It would be easy to fall victim to this foul weather.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
ITEM 8 1567
EXIT N 872
