NUMBER 866
NAME Crystal pillar
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
An odd formation of ice rises up here with many sharp crystals sticking out at unusual angles. It refracts the sunlight, sending forth a myriad of colorful rays of light that gives the whole place a strange ethereal beauty. To the north, a gleaming mountain range of ice looms like a massive behemoth.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CALL 16
ITEM 0 1271
ITEM 8 1567
EXTEND 0 of ice
*DESCRIPTION_START
 ITEM EXAM 0
This thing looks like a pillar of ice roughly six feet tall with sharp hexagonal crystals jutting out at odd angles along its length. It is capped by a large point, and its crystal clarity refracts the rays of the dim sun in a fashion that is extremely beautiful.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 873
EXIT S 856
EXIT E 867
EXIT W 865
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER Odd... you've never heard of formations like this forming naturally... usually they are grown, with a good deal of effort.
ENDIF
