*DESCRIPTION_START
Strong winds buffet you as you cling to the side of the mountain like a small insect holding onto the back of a galloping horse. Your every movement on the slope brings with it the danger of falling. From here, you can gaze out over the whole bleak plain. The sky, however, is filled with A brilliant aurora borealis in the shape of a lemniscate, whose beauty is truly breathtaking.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CHANNEL 853
REGION 51
CAVE
MINEB
;MONSTER_GROUP 84
item 8 1567

EXIT U 887
EXIT D 875
IFVERB RECALL -1
	IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
		ECHO PLAYER You effortlessly remember that a lemniscate is a figure-eight shaped curve whose equations in polar coordinates is p^2 = a^2 cos 20.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR SKILL32 < 6
		ECHO PLAYER You have no idea what a lemniscate is and wonder why you thought of it. A cruel GM trick probably.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB JUMP -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You are not suicidal.
ENDIF
IFVERB STAND -1
	EQUAL INTNUM7 0
ENDIF
IFVAR INTNUM7 = 0
	IFVAR DEAD = 0
		RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
		IFVAR DUMMY1 > 90
			ECHO PLAYER A gust of wind catches you off guard!
			SKILLCHECK 5 0 DUMMY1
			IFVAR DUMMY1 => 0
				ECHO PLAYER You manage to hang on to the slippery ice.
			ENDIF
			IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
				EQUAL INTNUM7 1
				ECHO PLAYER You lose your grip!
				ECHO OTHERS %N loses %h grip on the mountain and slides down.
				MOVE 875
				AFFECT 875
				ECHO OTHERS %N slides in.
				POSITION LAY
				DAMAGEPLR SLASH 10 You are scraped by the ice as you slide down.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	ECHO PLAYER You hear nothing except the howling of the wind.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB ASCEND -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER With these winds that probably wouldn't be a good idea.
ENDIF
;
